Czech Stocks Fall to Three-Month Low as CEZ, Erste, NWR Retreat

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-15T10:20:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/czech-stocks-fall-to-three-month-low-as-cez-erste-nwr-retreat.html
The Czech Republic’s main equity
index fell to its lowest in almost three months, led by declines
at  CEZ AS (CEZ) ,  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)  and  New World Resources NV. (NWR)   The PX gauge of 15 companies retreated for a second day,
losing 1.6 percent to 1,189.4 as of 10:55 a.m. in  Prague , its
lowest intraday level since Dec. 20.  CEZ, the country’s biggest power utility, lost 1.4 percent
to 791.5 koruna and Erste slumped 2.4 percent to 840 koruna, the
Austrian lender’s second day of declines. NWR slumped as much as
4.2 percent and last traded down 3.1 percent at 255.9 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
